Add to Cart Flow
User login karta hai aur token receive hota hai
User product page par “Add to Cart” button click karta hai
Frontend productId aur quantity backend ko send karta hai (with token)
Backend auth middleware token verify karke req.user._id set karta hai
Backend User ko database se find karta hai
User ke cart array ko check kiya jata hai:
Agar product already cart mein hai → quantity increase kar di jati hai
Agar product nahi hai → new item (productId + quantity) cart mein add hota hai
User document save ho jata hai
Cart API (GET) call par backend user ka cart return karta hai
populate("cart.product") se product details bhi attach ho jati hain
Frontend cart page par data display hota hai (name, price, quantity)

User Login hota hai
        ↓
CartContext automatically GET /api/cart call karta hai
        ↓
"Add to Cart" click → POST /api/cart { productId, quantity }
        ↓
Backend: User model ke andar "cart" array mein product add hota hai
        ↓
Cart dobara fetch hoti hai → UI update ho jata hai